# React & TypeScript Standards

## Component Structure
- Use **PascalCase** for component names and filenames [2, 3].
- Prefer functional components with `export default` for pages [1].

## TypeScript Usage
- No use of `any`. Define clear **Interfaces** for all Props [2, 3].
- ❌ `const MyComponent = (props: any) => { ... }`
- ✅ `interface MyComponentProps { title: string; }`

## Accessibility (a11y)
- All components must follow **WCAG 2.1** standards [2, 3].
- Use semantic HTML (e.g., `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<button>`).
- Images must have an `alt` attribute.

## Clean Code
- ❌ Never use magic numbers for status codes or constants [4, 5].
- ✅ Use constants from a central location.